      "QuestionText": "Suppose letters of alphabetical series are assigned values as follows: A = 1^1!, B = 2^2!, C = 3^3!, D = 4^4!and so on till Z = 26^26!, where x^y means x to the power of y and k! indicates factorial of k. What is the value of: (P - A) * (P - B) * (P - C) * ... * (P - Z)?",
      "Options": [
        {
          "OptionId": "A",
          "OptionText": "13^13!"
        },
        {
          "OptionId": "B",
          "OptionText": "25^25!"
        },
        {
          "OptionId": "C",
          "OptionText": "1!+2!+3!+\u202626!"
        },
        {
          "OptionId": "D",
          "OptionText": "None of these"
        }
      ],
      "Status": 1,
      "Remarks": null,
      "SubjectId": 20,
      "UniqueNodeId": 7068,
      "QuestionTypeId": 0,
      "QuestionId": 77780,
      "Explanation": "<span id=\"explanation77780\">P-P will be zero and the product also be zero.</span>",
      "Answer": "D",
      "Marks": 0
    },
